#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "File Formats"
msgstr "Formati datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:13
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Unless you choose to use a <link linkend=\"details.database\">relational "
#| "database</link>, &kappname; will store all your financial information in "
#| "a file ending in .kmy. Also, unless you use a <link linkend=\"firsttime."
#| "launch\">command line option</link> that tells it not to do so, when you "
#| "launch &kappname;, it will open the last file it had open. However, it is "
#| "important to know that there is more than one type of file &kappname; can "
#| "use to hold your financial data."
msgid ""
"Unless you choose to use a <link linkend=\"details.database\">relational "
"database</link>, &kmymoney; will store all your financial information in a "
"file. Most commonly, the file name will end in <filename class=\"extension"
"\">.kmy</filename>. Also, when you launch &kmymoney;, unless you use a <link "
"linkend=\"firsttime.launch\">command line option</link> that tells it not to "
"do so, it will open the last file it had open. However, it is important to "
"know that there is actually more than one type of file &kmymoney; can use to "
"hold your financial data."
msgstr ""
"Osim ukoliko odaberete da koristite <link linkend=\"details.database"
"\">relacionu bazu podataka</link>, &kappname; će spasiti sve vaše "
"finansijske informacije u datoteku koja završava sa .kmy. Također, osim ako "
"koristite <link linkend=\"firsttime.launch\">command line option</link> koja "
"mu govori da ne uradi tako, kada pokrenete &kappname;, otvoriće zadnju "
"datoteku koja je bila otvorena. Važno je da znate da postoji više od jednog "
"tipa datoteka u kojem &kappname; može čuvati vaše finansijske podatke."

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter describes the file formats in which &kmymoney; can store its "
"data in permanent form. It also discusses backing up your data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:29
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "File Formats"
msgid "Data File formats"
msgstr "Formati datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:30
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In general, &kmymoney; stores its information in form of an &XML; document. "
"Depending on the actual format, which is set in &kmymoney;'s configuration, "
"this &XML; document will be written: <itemizedlist> <listitem><para>as a "
"plain text file, encoded in UTF-8,</para></listitem> <listitem><para>as a "
"compressed file, using GZIP compression,</para></listitem> "
"<listitem><para>as an encrypted file, using GPG encryption, or</para></"
"listitem> <listitem> <para> as an anonymous plain text file, encoded in "
"UTF-8 but with all your personal data scrambled. </para> </listitem> </"
"itemizedlist> Each of these is described in more detail in the following "
"sections."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "Plain text file"
msgstr "Obična tekstualna datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:53
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This is the most space consuming format supported, as no compression is "
#| "performed. It is not intended for normal use, and is provided to support "
#| "debugging purposes and the capability to modify the file manually. If you "
#| "end a filename in <literal role=\"extension\">.xml</literal>, the file "
#| "will be stored in this format."
msgid ""
"This is the most space consuming format supported, as no compression is "
"performed. It is not intended for normal use, and is provided to support "
"debugging purposes and the capability to modify the file manually. If you "
"end a filename in <filename class=\"extension\">.xml</filename>, the file "
"will be stored in this format."
msgstr ""
"Ovo je format koji zauzima najviše memorije pošto ne dolazi do bilo kakve "
"kompresije. Nije namijenjeno za uobičajenu upotrebu i obezbijeđena je "
"podrška debugerskim potrebama i mogućnosti da se datoteka ručno modifikuje. "
"Ukoliko ime datoteke završite sa <literal role=\"extension\">.xml</literal>, "
"datoteka će biti sačuvana u ovom formatu."

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:61
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Manual modification of the file is not recommended to the normal user, "
#| "and should only be performed if the internal working of &kappname; is "
#| "fully understood or if instructions from the developers tell you what to "
#| "do. Don't blame the &kappname; developers if you screw up your data: You "
#| "have been warned!"
msgid ""
"Manual modification of the file is not recommended to the normal user, and "
"should only be performed if the internal working of &kmymoney; is fully "
"understood or if instructions from the developers tell you what to do. Don't "
"blame the &kmymoney; developers if you damage or destroy your data: You have "
"been warned!"
msgstr ""
"Ručna modifikacija datoteke nije preporučena uobičajenim korisnicima i treba "
"se raditi samo ukoliko u potpunosti poznajete kako &kappname; interno radi "
"ili ukoliko imate jasne instrukcije developera koje vam kažu šta da radite. "
"Nemojte kriviti &kappname; developere ukoliko korumpirate svoje podatke: "
"Upozoreni ste!"

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "GZIP-compressed file"
msgstr "GZIP-kompresovana datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:72
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This is the normal format used by &kappname; when you store a file with "
#| "the extension <literal role=\"extension\">.kmy</literal>."
msgid ""
"This is the normal format used by &kmymoney; when you store a file with the "
"extension <filename class=\"extension\">.kmy</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Ovo je uobičajeni format korišten u &kappname; kada spasite datoteku sa "
"ekstenzijom <literal role=\"extension\">.kmy</literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:78
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If <link linkend=\"details.formats.encrypted\">encryption</link> has been "
#| "selected, the file will be stored encrypted."
msgid ""
"If <link linkend=\"details.formats.encrypted\">encryption</link> has been "
"selected in the configuration, the file will be stored encrypted, as "
"described in the next section."
msgstr ""
"Ukoliko je <link linkend=\"details.formats.encrypted\">enkripcija</link> "
"odabrana, datoteka će biti kodirana i spašena."

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:85
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you want to look at the contents of a GZIP compressed file, rename it "
#| "to a filename ending in <literal role=\"extension\">.gz</literal> (&eg;, "
#| "rename <filename>myfinances.kmy</filename> to <filename>myfinances.kmy."
#| "gz</filename>), then use <command>gunzip</command> to uncompress the file "
#| "and look at it. You don't have to compress it before loading it into "
#| "&kappname; the next time, because &kappname; can read the uncompressed "
#| "data as well. Nevertheless, if you save it thereafter, it will be saved "
#| "compressed again. Use the <link linkend=\"details.formats.plain\">.xml</"
#| "link> extension to write it in uncompressed format."
msgid ""
"If you want to look at the contents of a GZIP compressed file, rename it to "
"a filename ending in <filename class=\"extension\">.gz</filename> (&eg;, "
"rename <filename>myfinances.kmy</filename> to <filename>myfinances.kmy.gz</"
"filename>), then use <command>gunzip</command> to uncompress the file and "
"look at it. You don't have to compress it before loading it into &kmymoney; "
"the next time, because &kmymoney; can read the uncompressed data as well. "
"Nevertheless, if you save it thereafter, it will be saved compressed again. "
"Use the <link linkend=\"details.formats.plain\"><filename class=\"extension"
"\">.xml</filename></link> extension to write it in uncompressed format."
msgstr ""
"Ukoliko želite da pogledate sadržaj GZIP kompresovane datoteke, preimenujte "
"kraj imena datoteke u <literal role=\"extension\">.gz</literal> (&eg;, "
"rename <filename>myfinances.kmy</filename> u <filename>myfinances.kmy.gz</"
"filename>), onda upotrijebite <command>gunzip</command> da ekstraktujete "
"datoteku kako biste je mogli pregledati. Ne morate je kompresovati da biste "
"je otvorili u &kappname;  zato što &kappname; također može očitati "
"nekompresovane podatke. Ukoliko ga spasite odmah, opet će biti prvo "
"kompresovano pa sačuvano. Upotrijebite <link linkend=\"details.formats.plain"
"\">.xml</link> ekstenziju ukoliko želite pisati u nekompresovanom formatu."

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid "GPG-encrypted file"
msgstr "GPG-kodirana datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:99
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Using the GPG-encrypted file format is a very secure method of storing "
#| "your personal finance data on your storage device. When &kappname; has "
#| "been instructed through the settings dialog to store your data encrypted, "
#| "it will cipher the data using GPG and the key you provided before "
#| "actually storing it. When opening an encrypted file, you have to provide "
#| "the passphrase necessary to open your keyring. The encrypted file itself "
#| "will be stored in GPG's <emphasis>ASCII armored</emphasis> format."
msgid ""
"Using the GPG-encrypted file format is a very secure method of storing your "
"personal finance data on your storage device. When &kmymoney; has been "
"instructed through the settings dialog to store your data encrypted, it will "
"cipher the data using GPG and the key you provided before actually storing "
"it. When opening an encrypted file, you have to provide the passphrase "
"necessary to open your keyring. The encrypted file itself will be stored in "
"GPG's <emphasis>&ASCII; armored</emphasis> format."
msgstr ""
"Upotreba formata GPG-kodirane datoteke je veoma sigurna metoda spašavanja "
"osobnih finansijskih podataka na uređaj za skladištenje. Kada &kappname; "
"dobije instrukcije u dijalogu za postavke da vaše podatke kodira pa spasi, "
"kodiraće podatke upotrebom GPG i ključa koji vi morate unijeti prije nego "
"što se podaci stvarno spase. Prilikom otvaranja kodirane datoteke, morate "
"unijeti ključ koji ste prethodno naveli. Sama datoteka će biti spašena u GPG "
"<emphasis>ASCII armored</emphasis> formatu."

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:108
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "When using GPG encryption, GPG also compresses the file, so no extra "
#| "compression is necessary."
msgid ""
"When using GPG encryption, GPG also compresses the file using gzip, so no "
"extra compression is necessary."
msgstr ""
"Prilikom upotrebe GPG kodiranja, GPG također kompresuje datoteku pa dodatna "
"kompresija nije potrebna."

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "GPG-Keys"
msgstr "GPG-ključevi"

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:116
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you have not done so already for mail encryption, you need to generate "
#| "a key-pair in order to use the GPG encryption feature of &kappname;. "
#| "Also, <application>GPG</application> must be installed on your system."
msgid ""
"If you have not done so already for mail encryption, you need to generate a "
"key-pair in order to use the GPG encryption feature of &kmymoney;. Also, "
"<application>GPG</application> must be installed on your system."
msgstr ""
"Ukoliko niste već uradili nešto slično za kodiranje emaila, morate "
"generisati par-ključeva da biste koristili opciju GPG kodiranja u "
"&kappname;. Također, <application>GPG</application> mora biti instalirana na "
"vašem sistemu."

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:122
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The details about how to generate a key-pair and how to take care of it "
#| "are beyond the scope of this document. A Mini Howto on this subject can "
#| "be found at <ulink url=\"http://www.gnupg.org/documentation/howtos.en.html"
#| "\">http://www.gnupg.org/documentation/howtos.en.html</ulink>."
msgid ""
"The details about how to generate a key-pair and how to take care of it are "
"beyond the scope of this document. A Mini Howto on this subject can be found "
"at <ulink url=\"https://www.gnupg.org/documentation/howtos.en.html\">https://"
"www.gnupg.org/documentation/howtos.en.html</ulink>. The web sites of most "
"&Linux; distributions also contain instructions on using GPG in that "
"distribution."
msgstr ""
"Detalji o tome kako da generišete par-ključeva i kako da ih tretirate izlaze "
"van opsega ovog dokumenta. Jednostavni tutorijal na ovu temu možete pronaći "
"na <ulink url=\"http://www.gnupg.org/documentation/howtos.en.html\">http://"
"www.gnupg.org/documentation/howtos.en.html</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:131
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Setting the keys in &kappname;"
msgid "Setting the keys in &kmymoney;"
msgstr "Postavljanje ključeva u &kappname;"

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:132
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "On the encryption page of the settings dialog, there is a drop down list "
#| "where you can select the key that should be used for encryption and "
#| "decryption. Additionally you can find a field where you can enter the key-"
#| "id of a key not in the listbox. You can use either the key-id, the email "
#| "address associated with this key, or any other valid GPG key "
#| "identification as the value for this field. When you enter the key-id, "
#| "&kappname; will check its validity and display a green LED icon in the "
#| "dialog if a key is found."
msgid ""
"On the encryption page of the settings dialog, there is a dropdown list "
"where you can select the key that should be used for encryption and "
"decryption. Additionally, there is a field where you can enter the key-id of "
"a key not in the listbox. You can use either the key-id, the email address "
"associated with this key, or any other valid GPG key identification as the "
"value for this field. When you enter the key-id, &kmymoney; will check its "
"validity and display a green LED icon in the dialog if a key is found."
msgstr ""
"Na stranici kodiranja u dijalogu postavki postoji opadajuća lista gdje "
"možete odabrati ključ koji će se koristiti za kodiranje i dekodiranje. "
"Također možete naći polje u koje možete unijeti id-ključa van liste.Možete "
"koristiti ili id-ključa, email adresu koja je povezana sa ovim ključem ili "
"bilo koju drugu validnu GPG ključ identifikaciju kao vrijednost ovog polja. "
"Kada unesete id-ključa, &kappname; će provjeriti da li je validan i "
"prikazati zelenu LED ikonu u dijalogu ukoliko jeste."

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure you have both the public and the private key for this id. If you "
"do not own the private key for the id entered, you will not be able to open "
"the file again."
msgstr ""
"Budite sigurni da imate i javni i privatni ključ za ovaj id. Ukoliko ne "
"posjedujete privatni ključ za id koji ste unijeli, nećete moći otvoriti "
"datoteku ponovo."

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:150
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "The &kappname; recover key"
msgid "The &kmymoney; recovery key"
msgstr "&kappname; ključ za oporavak"

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:151
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Also on this page of the settings dialog you have the choice of selecting "
#| "supplemental encryption with the &kappname; recover key. This option is "
#| "available to you if that key is stored in your <application>GPG</"
#| "application> keyring. Selecting this option will allow you to recover "
#| "your data even in the case you lose your own private key. This is "
#| "possible because the data is not only encrypted for your own key, but "
#| "also for the &kappname; recover key. This key is only available to "
#| "selected &kappname; developers (at the time of writing only to the "
#| "author). As of the release of &kappname; version 4.7, the recover key is "
#| "set to expire on 3 January 2015."
msgid ""
"Also on this page of the settings dialog you have the choice of selecting "
"supplemental encryption with the &kmymoney; recovery key. This option is "
"available to you if that key is stored in your <application>GPG</"
"application> keyring. Selecting this option will allow you to recover your "
"data even in the case you lose your own private key. This is possible "
"because the data is not only encrypted for your own key, but also for the "
"&kmymoney; recovery key. This key is only available to selected &kmymoney; "
"developers (at the time of writing only to the author.) As of the May, 2024, "
"the recovery key is set to expire on 7 January 2025."
msgstr ""
"Na ovoj stranici dijaloga postavki imate pravo izbora dopunskog kodiranja sa "
"&kappname; ključem za oporavak. Ova opcija vam je omogućena ukoliko je taj "
"ključ spašen medju vašim <application>GPG</application> ključevima. Odabir "
"ove opcije će vam omogućiti da povratite podatke čak i u slučaju gubljenja "
"privatnog ključa. Ovo je moguće zato što podaci nisu kodirani samo za vaš "
"privatni ključ nego i za ključ za oporavak. Ovaj ključ je dostupan samo "
"odabranim &kappname; developerima(prilikom pisanja samo autoru). Od puštanja "
"&kappname; verzije 4.7 u upotrebu, ključ za oporavak je podešen da istekne "
"treceg januara 2015."

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:162
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Under normal circumstances, you will open/save/close your file as usual. "
#| "In the abnormal case of loss of your key, you have the chance to contact "
#| "one of the developers who has access to the &kappname; recover key and "
#| "request help to recover your data. You may contact the developers via "
#| "email to the &kappname; developer mailing list at &devlist;."
msgid ""
"Under normal circumstances, you will open/save/close your file as usual. In "
"the abnormal case of loss of your key, you have the chance to contact one of "
"the developers who has access to the &kmymoney; recover key and request help "
"to recover your data. You may contact the developers via email to the "
"&kmymoney; developer mailing list at &devlist;."
msgstr ""
"Pod uobičajenim okolnostima, možete otvoriti/spasiti/zatvoriti vašu datoteku "
"kao i uvijek. U specijalnim slučajevima kada izgubite svoj ključ, možete "
"kontaktirati jednog od developera koji ima pristup &kappname; ključu za "
"oporavak i možete tražiti da vam pomogne povratiti sve podatke. Developere "
"možete kontaktirati putem emaila &kappname; mail listi developera na "
"&devlist;."

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To get the recovery key, go to <ulink url=\"https://kmymoney.org/recovery."
"html\"> The KMyMoney recovery key</ulink> page of the &kmymoney; web site. "
"Copy and save the <quote>PGP PUBLIC KEY BLOCK</quote> (including the "
"<quote>BEGIN</quote> and <quote>END</quote> lines) to a text file and then "
"import it with gpg."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remember that the developer can only help recover your data file if you "
"actually do encrypt it with the recovery key, in addition to your own key."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid "Anonymous file"
msgstr "Anonimna datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:185
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This format is not intended to be used for normal data storage. It is "
#| "supported so that in case of a problem, you can supply the &kappname; "
#| "development team with your file without disclosing any of the "
#| "confidential details in your financial data. For example, it changes "
#| "institution, account, payee, and category names to strings such as "
#| "\"I000001\" and \"A000001,\" it makes similar changes to all data such as "
#| "account numbers, and it also randomly changes the amounts of transactions."
msgid ""
"This format is not intended to be used for normal data storage. It is "
"supported so that in case of a problem, you can supply the &kmymoney; "
"development team with your file without disclosing any of the confidential "
"details in your financial data. For example, it changes institution, "
"account, payee, and category names to strings such as \"I000001\" and "
"\"A000001\"; it makes similar changes to all data such as account numbers, "
"and it also randomly changes the amounts of transactions."
msgstr ""
"Ovaj format nije namijenjen za uobičajeno spašavanje podataka. Podržan je "
"kako bi u slučaju problema mogli &kappname; developerskom timu poslati svoju "
"datoteku bez otkrivanja povjerljivih detalja o vašim finansijskim podacima. "
"Npr., mijenja institucije, račune, primaoce i kategorije u stringove kao što "
"su \"I000001\" i \"A000001\", te radi slične promjene nad svim podacima kao "
"što su brojevi računa i također nasumično mijenja vrijednosti transakcija."

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:194
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If instructed by the developers, use the <guimenuitem>Save as...</"
#| "guimenuitem> menu item to store your data in anonymous format by "
#| "selecting <literal role=\"filter\">Anonymous files</literal> as the "
#| "filter. This also changes the file extension to <literal role=\"extension"
#| "\">.anon.xml</literal>."
msgid ""
"If instructed by the developers, use the <guimenuitem>Save as...</"
"guimenuitem> menu item to store your data in anonymous format by selecting "
"<literal role=\"filter\">Anonymous files</literal> as the filter. This also "
"changes the file extension to <filename class=\"extension\">.anon.xml</"
"filename>."
msgstr ""
"Ukoliko je naznačeno od strane developera, koristite <guimenuitem>Save as..."
"</guimenuitem> meni stavku kako biste spasili podatke u anonimnom formatu "
"klikom na <literal role=\"filter\">Anonymous files</literal> kao filter. Ovo "
"također mijenja ekstenziju datoteke u <literal role=\"extension\">.anon.xml</"
"literal>."

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:201
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To verify that your problem still exists, reload this anonymized file and "
"try to duplicate your problem. If the problem is still present, send the "
"file to the developer mailing list at &devlist; for further investigation. "
"If the problem does not show ... well, I don't want to think about this "
"scenario right now."
msgstr ""
"Da biste provjerili da li problem i dalje postoji, ponovo otvorite ovu "
"anonimnu datoteku i pokušajte duplicirati problem. Ukoliko problem idalje "
"postoji, pošaljite datoteku na developer email listu za daljnju istragu. "
"Ukoliko problem ne bude više postojao . . . pa, ne bih da razmišljam o tom "
"scenariju baš sada."

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:209
#, no-c-format
msgid "Data file locations"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All of the above file types can be stored on a local hard drive, a removable "
"device such as a usb thumb drive, or a network location. Depending on your "
"Operating System, a remote location may need to be mapped or mounted prior "
"to use."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:216
#, no-c-format
msgid "Limitation on Windows"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On &Windows;, in order to use a network or remote file location, that mapped "
"location must be mapped to a drive letter."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:226
#, no-c-format
msgid "Backup"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:227
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We will not attempt here to convince you that making backup copies of your "
"data is an extremely good idea; hopefully you are already convinced of that. "
"This section describes three ways to do this, and you can use any one, two, "
"or even all three of them. Note that this is about backing up a data file; "
"if you use an SQL backend to store your data, see the documentation for that "
"database system for instructions on making backups."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "Backup file location"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you need a backup copy of your data to confirm some aspect of your "
"finances at a previous point in time, or to revert to an earlier state, such "
"as to undo importing a lot of data to the wrong account, it doesn't matter "
"whether the backup copy is local or stored elsewhere, such as on an attached "
"network drive. However, if you need a backup to recover from loss of data if "
"you disk drive failed, for example, it is essential that the backup is "
"<emphasis>not</emphasis> on the same drive as your primary data file. In "
"case of a larger disaster, such as a house fire, you would need a backup "
"copy stored in a fireproof safe or at a physically different location. "
"Please keep this in mind as you establish your backup strategy."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:250
#, no-c-format
msgid "Autosave"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kmymoney; has the ability to automatically save a copy of your data file at "
"regular intervals. It can also do so on closing the program, if the data has "
"changed. This behavior can be configured on the &kmymoney; <link linkend="
"\"details.settings.general.global\">configuration dialog, General section, "
"Global tab</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "File copy"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:261
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Unless you are using SQL storage, your data may be compressed, and it may be "
"encrypted, but is kept in a regular file. Whenever you save your data with "
"the <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Save</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item, it writes all your data to a file, replacing the "
"previous version. The most straightforward way of backing up your data is by "
"making a copy of that file. A single copy can even have the same file name "
"if it is in a different folder than your original file, but if you are going "
"to keep multiple copies, it makes sense to include some version of the "
"current date and time in each file name. You can save these to a network "
"drive, or to a USB storage device, or even to an optical device. The primary "
"downside of this method is that you need to keep track of all the backups, "
"but it does provide the most flexibility."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: details-formats.docbook:276
#, no-c-format
msgid "Backup command"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:277
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To make things a bit easier, you can select the <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Backup</guimenuitem> </menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: details-formats.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>file backup</screeninfo>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: details-formats.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>file backup</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you click <guibutton>OK</guibutton> &kmymoney; will create a copy of "
"your data file, with the date (formatted as YYYY-MM-DD) appended to the "
"name. Note that this means only one backup per day can be created by this "
"method. If you have already created a backup on the same day, &kmymoney; "
"will ask if you want to replace the previous backup or cancel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:302
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kmymoney; will save this file to the directory specified in the "
"<guilabel>Mount Point</guilabel> field. You can either manually type the "
"full path to the directory or click <guibutton>Choose...</guibutton> and "
"navigate to it using the file browser. The directory can be on a local "
"storage device or it can be a network folder."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: details-formats.docbook:310
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the specified directory is actually a mount point for a storage device "
"that is not always mounted, you can check the <guilabel>Mount this directory "
"before backing up</guilabel> checkbox. Do not use this for a regular network "
"file share which is always mounted."
msgstr ""

